n the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Bozum was born about 1355, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Bozum, was 22 and his mother, Baroness Ida Cornwall, was 17. He married Jane St. George about 1370. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1355–":"umbes 1355–Surnud","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1374–1424":"1374–1424","1355–1387":"1355–1387","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1334–1380":"1334–1380","1340–1373":"1340–1373","about 1370":"umbes 1370","1374":"1374","1373":"1373","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1424":"1424","Abt 1370":"umbes 1370","Abt 1355":"umbes 1355","1334":"1334","1355":"1355","1387":"1387","Abt 1380":"umbes 1380","1408":"1408","Bozom Zeal, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","South Tawton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"South Tawton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","of Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1355–":"noin 1355–Kuollut","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1374–1424":"1374–1424","1355–1387":"1355–1387","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1334–1380":"1334–1380","1340–1373":"1340–1373","about 1370":"noin 1370","1374":"1374","1373":"1373","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1424":"1424","Abt 1370":"noin 1370","Abt 1355":"noin 1355","1334":"1334","1355":"1355","1387":"1387","Abt 1380":"noin 1380","1408":"1408","Bozom Zeal, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","South Tawton, Devon, Engl